cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it introduces a new type of neural network, the quaternion-valued recurrent projection neural network (QRPNN), which is a combination of non-local projection learning and quaternion-valued recurrent correlation neural network (QRCNN). It also compares the performance of QRPNNs with QRCNNs in terms of storage capacity and noise tolerance, which are important aspects of neural network design. 

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with the design and optimization of neural networks. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely category as the paper introduces a new type of neural network that can be used for associative memories, which is a common application of AI. 

Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) is also a possible category as the paper deals with multi-dimensional data, which is often encountered in computer vision tasks. 

Finally, the paper involves Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) as it deals with the processing of multi-dimensional data using neural networks.
